# Builder.io Rules - UI5 Design System

This project exclusively uses SAP UI5 Web Components. All AI-generated code and human contributions must follow these principles.

## Core Principles

### 1. UI5 Components First
**Always use UI5 web components for any user interface element.**

- ✅ Use `<ui5-button>`, `<ui5-input>`, `<ui5-dialog>`, etc.
- ❌ Never use other UI frameworks (Angular Material, Bootstrap, etc.)
- ❌ Never use plain HTML elements for interactive UI (`<button>`, `<input>`, etc.)

**Decision Tree for UI Components:**
1. Is there a UI5 component for this? → Use it
2. Can multiple UI5 components be combined? → Combine them
3. Is this purely layout/structure? → Use semantic HTML (`<div>`, `<section>`, etc.)
4. Still no solution? → Ask for guidance before creating custom components

### 2. Import Verification
**Every UI5 component used in templates must be imported in `app.module.ts`.**

- Import individual components from dist paths: `import '@ui5/webcomponents/dist/Button';`
- Import Fiori components from: `import '@ui5/webcomponents-fiori/dist/ShellBar';`
- Import icons individually: `import '@ui5/webcomponents-icons/dist/palette.js';`
- Never import entire packages (causes bundle bloat)

### 3. Angular Integration
**Use Angular best practices when integrating UI5 components.**

- Add `CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA` to `@NgModule` schemas
- Use `@ViewChild` with `ElementRef` to access UI5 component instances
- UI5 events use `event.detail` for custom data
- Access properties/methods via `nativeElement`: `this.button.nativeElement.show()`

### 4. Theme Consistency
**Maintain consistent UI5 theming throughout the application.**

- Set theme using `setTheme('sap_horizon')` in `app.module.ts`
- Configure `xx-wc-no-conflict` in `index.html` to prevent event conflicts
- Use valid UI5 theme names only (sap_horizon, sap_fiori_3, etc.)

### 5. Styling with UI5 Design Tokens
**Leverage UI5's built-in design system rather than custom CSS.**

- Use UI5 component properties for styling: `design="Emphasized"`, `state="Success"`
- Use CSS variables from UI5 theme when custom styling is needed
- Avoid overriding UI5 component internal styles
- Keep custom CSS minimal and focused on layout/spacing

## Operating Principles

### Code Quality
- **Simplicity**: Don't over-engineer. Use the simplest UI5 component that solves the problem
- **Consistency**: All similar UI patterns should use the same UI5 components
- **Accessibility**: UI5 components have built-in accessibility - leverage it
- **Performance**: Import only components you use to minimize bundle size

### TypeScript Safety
- Use proper types when accessing UI5 components via `ElementRef`
- Define interfaces for UI5 event detail objects when needed
- Avoid `any` types - use specific types or create them

### Testing Baseline
- Test UI5 component integration in Angular components
- Verify event handlers work correctly with UI5's event system
- Test responsive behavior of UI5 components

### Documentation
- Comment complex UI5 component configurations
- Document custom event handlers that use `event.detail`
- Link to official UI5 docs when using advanced component features

## Common Patterns

### Form Inputs

<ui5-input 
  placeholder="Enter value"
  (input)="onInput($event)">
</ui5-input>
```

```typescript
onInput(event: any) {
  const value = event.target.value;
  // Process input
}
```

### Dialogs and Popovers
```html
<ui5-dialog #myDialog header-text="Title">
  <ui5-label>Content</ui5-label>
  <ui5-button slot="footer" (click)="myDialog.close()">Close</ui5-button>
</ui5-dialog>
```

```typescript
@ViewChild('myDialog') dialog: ElementRef;

openDialog() {
  this.dialog.nativeElement.show();
}
```

### Lists with Items
```html
<ui5-list>
  <ui5-li *ngFor="let item of items">{{ item.name }}</ui5-li>
</ui5-list>
```

### ShellBar Navigation
```html
<ui5-shellbar
  primary-title="My App"
  (profile-click)="onProfileClick($event)">
  <ui5-shellbar-item text="Settings" icon="settings"></ui5-shellbar-item>
</ui5-shellbar>
```

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### ❌ Mixing UI Frameworks
```html
<!-- WRONG: Don't mix UI5 with Material or other frameworks -->
<ui5-button>UI5 Button</ui5-button>
<button mat-button>Material Button</button>
```

### ❌ Using Plain HTML Interactive Elements
```html
<!-- WRONG: Don't use plain buttons/inputs -->
<button onclick="doSomething()">Click</button>
<input type="text" placeholder="Name">

<!-- RIGHT: Use UI5 components -->
<ui5-button (click)="doSomething()">Click</ui5-button>
<ui5-input placeholder="Name"></ui5-input>
```

### ❌ Importing Entire Packages
```typescript
// WRONG: Imports all components
import '@ui5/webcomponents';

// RIGHT: Import only what you need
import '@ui5/webcomponents/dist/Button';
import '@ui5/webcomponents/dist/Input';
```

### ❌ Missing CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA
```typescript
// WRONG: No schema for custom elements
@NgModule({
  declarations: [AppComponent],
  imports: [BrowserModule]
})

// RIGHT: Include schema
@NgModule({
  declarations: [AppComponent],
  imports: [BrowserModule],
  schemas: [CUSTOM_ELEMENTS_SCHEMA]
})
```

